  "text": "The ICE during trait method resolution occurs in the Rust compiler's method resolution system. There are two main components: (1) trait method candidate collection in rustc_trait_selection, and (2) method resolution with candidate assembly in rustc_hir_typeck.\n\nIn rustc_trait_selection (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs), the assemble_candidates function (line 27) collects trait impl candidates for trait resolution. It handles the ambiguous field in SelectionCandidateSet to track ambiguous candidate situations (line 53).\n\nIn rustc_hir_typeck, method resolution happens in multiple stages:\n1. Candidate assembly in probe.rs collects inherent and extension candidates:\n   - assemble_inherent_candidates (line 802) collects methods from inherent impls\n   - assemble_inherent_candidates_for_incoherent_ty (line 871) handles incoherent types\n   - assemble_extension_candidates_for_traits_in_scope (line 1011) collects trait methods in scope\n   - assemble_extension_candidates_for_all_traits (line 1028) collects all trait methods\n\n2. Candidate filtering in consider_candidates (line 1676) filters the candidates and returns MethodError::Ambiguity (lines 1471, 1741) when multiple candidates match.\n\n3. Error reporting in suggest.rs handles MethodError::Ambiguity (line 221) with error code E0034 (\"multiple applicable items in scope\").\n\n4. The MethodError enum definition in mod.rs (line 49) defines the Ambiguity variant.\n\nA potential ICE location is in confirm.rs (line 222) where a panic occurs if the receiver type cannot be adjusted to const ptr, which could happen during trait method confirmation if the type inference produces unexpected types during candidate collection."
